1 Section 2. The Kentucky General Assembly emphasizes the critical role of AM
2 radio in serving the informational needs of rural communities, supporting the agriculture
3 industry, and enhancing emergency preparedness.
4 Section 3. The Kentucky General Assembly urges the federal government to
5 ensure continued accessibility to AM radio in vehicles through the passage of the AM
6 Radio for Every Vehicle Act of 2025 and policies that maintain its crucial role.
7 Section 4. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
8 copy of this Resolution to the Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, the
9 Majority Leader of the United States Senate, and each member of the Kentucky
10 congressional delegation.
